### Identity Service — Users Endpoints
### Requires: REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)
### Step 1: Run login in auth.http first, then paste your access_token below

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8002

# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Set your access_token here after logging in
# ──────────────────────────────────────────
@accessToken = PASTE_YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# GET /api/v1/users/me
# ──────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Get current authenticated user profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 2. Get /me with no token → expect 403 Forbidden
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me

###

### 3. Get /me with invalid token → expect 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me
Authorization: Bearer this.is.invalid

# ──────────────────────────────────────────
# GET /api/v1/users/{user_id}
# ──────────────────────────────────────────

###

### 4. Get user by ID — paste a valid UUID from a previous register/login response
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/PASTE_USER_UUID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 5. Get user with non-existent UUID → expect 404 Not Found
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 6. Get user with malformed UUID → expect 422 Unprocessable Entity
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/not-a-valid-uuid
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
